# Swift Style

- Follow Swift 6 and Swift API Design Guidelines.
- Prefer `@Observable` over `ObservableObject` for ViewModels.
- Use explicit types where clarity helps; infer elsewhere.
- See `.cursor/rules/platform/ios-always.mdc` and root rules for full conventions.
